    "affected_item": "Environment Geometry (Terrain Mesh)"
}

{
    "reasoning": "In the screenshot there is an NPC crouching directly behind the horse on the right, but most of the character’s body (head and torso) is clipped inside the horse’s mesh and rendered invisible. This indicates a collision or animation blending issue where the character model is intersecting the horse without proper occlusion or separation.",
    "bug_report_title": "Crouching NPC Clips and Becomes Invisible Inside Horse Mesh",
    "bug_report_description": "When an NPC crouches directly behind a mounted horse, the character model clips into the horse’s geometry. As a result, the NPC’s head and upper body are not rendered, making the soldier appear to vanish. This visual glitch can be distracting, breaks immersion, and may hide the presence of friendly units in the field.",
    "affected_item": "NPC character model"
}

{
    "reasoning": "The player character’s arms and weapon are visibly intersecting the door mesh rather than being occluded or pushed aside, indicating an animation or collision mismatch between the door and the character model.",
